<D>__{no offense, no offense, i told you i liked the boat.}
<P>__{(to fran)}
<D>__{what is he, a touchy fella...?}
<C>__{fran}
<D>__{you have to ask him.}
<C>__{florid man}
<P>__{(to moore)}
<D>__{what i'd like to do: i will take'er out again, me and some people... the weekend...?}
<A>__{fran, in the b.g. comes down the gangplank.}
<C>__{moore}
<D>__{...we'll be here...}
<A>__{angle, on fran, as she turns her back on the florid man, and stands close to moore, her face surprised, moore ignores her.}
<C>__{moore }
<D>__{...we'll be here.}
<C>__{florid man}
<D>__{...i like this boat...}
<C>__{fran}
<D>__{...mister fletcher, tell you what, you put down your deposit, we're gonna fit you one out. your specs.}
<C>__{florid man}
<D>__{i don't want you, fit me one out, i want to buy this one here. this is a hell of a boat.}
<C>__{fran}
<D>__{well, this one's not for sale.}
<C>__{florid man}
<D>__{everything's for sale. i'm gone tell you what: you want, sell the boat to me, this weekend, you want to name your price, we'll...}
<P>__{(he hands fran a business card and scribbles on the back of it.)}
